#EkoAtlantic Heinrich Boll country director is giving closing remarks.Says the discussions were eye-opening. Hopes concerns will b addressed
#EkoAtlantic Env. Comm says flooding problems in Maiyegun and Alpha Beach was caused by shipwrecks and not the #EkoAtlantic project
#EkoAtlantic Env. Comm says LASG would continue to work & protect properties along coastlines & concerns will be channeled to the governor.
#EkoAtlantic Prof. Awosika says communities and stakeholders shd collaborate with NOI in their independent surveillance activities
#EkoAtlantic Another FG official says Fed. Min. of Env. shd not be blamed as they have done their best with regard to the project's EIA
#EkoAtlantic A local leader says new mitigation measures shd be explored and considered.
#EkoAtlantic Another participant says policy makers shd start thinking about serving the people.
#EkoAtlantic UNDP representative says UNDP is prepared to partner with LASG on long-term planning, and sustainable devt. in Lagos State
#EkoAtlantic A Fed. Govt official says FG shd not be blamed because Nigeria is a lawless country. And that one arm of govt shd not be blamed
#EkoAtlantic Another participant says EIA does not have all the solutions...It only gives insight into potential risks and problems.
#EkoAtlantic Another participant tells the commissioner that he shd not view objections by stakeholders as an affront to the project.
#EkoAtlantic  ...about rising sea levels, about global warming, and incessant flooding. Nigeria must start doing same.
#EkoAtlantic Another participant is talking abt climate change. Coastal cities all over the world are building awareness abt heavier rains..
#EkoAtlantic Participants says the current revetment is faulty. There shd  be some distance between the revetment and the sea.
#EkoAtlantic Another participant is indicting the Fed. Min. of Env. He says the revetment is supposed to absorb shock, not repel shock.
#EkoAtlantic A participant says the seas are gonna get more violent, and the oceans will keep surging...This means protection must increase
#EkoAtlantic Amadi says new EIA should address social issues, affecting coastal communities. The old EIA did not.
#EkoAtlantic Prof Amadi says shoreline must be heavily surrounded with vegetation. Recommends that a marine park be built around the project
#EkoAtlantic Amadi says leaders travel abroad and see nice things, & try to impose it on their own communities, without thinking abt context
#EkoAtlantic Prof Ako Amadi is presenting a 7-point agenda listing best practices 4 managing such projects. It will take 7 yrs to implement.
#EkoAtlantic Env. Comm says everywhere in the world, properties near waterfronts are not affordable, and not meant for the poor.
